<br>
On most <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> community</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> raids I've been on (3 servers) the loot tends to be NBG random, meaning roll away if you can and will use something that drops.  Rolling against people who legitimately need an upgrade when you are just going to sell an item for plat is just wrong (thats my opinion and its broadly but not completely shared).  <br>
<br>
On most servers, most raid loot is no-drop so selling it is not an issue, I guess its more of a problem here... Never thought of that when I started a character here.<br>
<br>
So you won it, you used it and lucked out and got an upgrade a week later ?  Its yours, sell it IMO, I dont care at that point.  But it does piss me off to see someone take an item NBG then have it up for sale in the Bazaar 2 hours later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthraallfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThraallFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 1:42:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1493.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I´m an ignorant loot hore</span><hr size=1> Its an issue if you get the piece of loot and then turn around and sell it the next day or next week.  However imo if you sell it a month later its most likely all fair.  in a month its perfectly reasonable to get an upgrade.<br>
<br>
The reason its frowned upon for selling loot you get on a raid is because when you roll on it (assuming NBG) it means you will WEAR the gear and USE it not turn around and SELL it.<br>
