 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170394  target="web">Thraall Oracle of the North</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1053<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 4:19:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1493.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The real reason is that ..</span><hr size=1> .. if you roll on a class-restricted item and then turn around and sell it, you have just basically stolen the item from all those people that didn't get a chance to roll; eg. only bards are permitted to roll on the drum from naggy.  If the bard that wins sells it the next day, she's just doing what anyone could have done and is thus ripping off all the rest there that were not permitted to roll on it.  By rolling on a restricted item, you're basically agreeing to actually put that item to a use that those not permitted to roll on it can't or won't do.  This is why folks talk about item utility for loot.  Utility is just a quick way to say &quot;amount of usage that item will see before being sold&quot;.<br>
<br>
As to why not treat everything as trade-bait, well, some do.  It's really just a matter of personal values.  However, most people you will meet in EQ value obtaining their items directly much higher than obtaining them via trades or purchases.  Prestige for fighters, plat for merchants.  Been that way for humans since forever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 487<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 11:39:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1493.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The real reason is that ..</span><hr size=1> eventually all of your gear will get upgraded but it's a bad idea to instantly turn around and resell an item you got on the pretense that you would use it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urubisthenome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rubis the Nome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 2:08:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1493.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The real reason is that ..</span><hr size=1> ARGH!!!11!1!!1<br>
